CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 21, 1956, pg. A24, reads: "'ANT' Girls - These happy young ladies are members of a newly organized sorority at Oliver High School. They aren't telling was 'ANT' means; it's a secret.  Left to right, on the floor: Theresa Boxley and Bessie Mathews.  Second row: Shirley Boxley, Helen Goodnight, Larene Taylor, Ruth Sodney, Ceceli Watson and Dorothy Snyder.  Third row: Mary Jane Rutherford, Barbara Betts, Betty Marshall, Isabella Hendricks, Rosia Lee Roberts and Beverly Johnson.  Not pictured were Alice Hill and Travis Moorehead. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of ANT club members, from left on floor: Theresa Boxley, Bessie Mathews; second row: Shirley Boxley, Helen Goodnight, Larene Taylor, Ruth Sodney, Ceceli Watson, and Dorothy Snyder; third row: Mary Jane Rutherford, Barbara Betts, Betty Marshall, Isabella Hendricks, Rosia Lee Roberts, and Beverly Johnson, horizontal format
